## Output structure (MANDATORY 10 sections)

```markdown
# Intake — <title>

## 1. Problem statement
- Symptom
- Root cause (as stated)
- Impact

## 2. Scope

### In scope
- bullet list

### Out of scope (explicit)
- bullet list — what we will NOT touch in this work item

## 3. Constraints (from seed + inferred)
- bullet list

## 4. Success criteria
- ≥ 3 verifiable criteria (use ✅ prefix per criterion)

## 5. Measurement / acceptance plan
- How will we know each success criterion is satisfied
- Mark any "Unknown" measurement methods explicitly

## 6. Decisions to lock in now (irreversible-ish)
- For each: what was decided + why irreversible + alternatives considered

## 7. Reversible decisions (defer to design stage)
- For each: brief description, deferred owner

## 8. Risks

| Risk | Likelihood | Severity | Mitigation |
|---|---|---|---|

## 9. Unknowns / open questions
- U1, U2, ... numbered; each is a concrete investigation, not a vague worry

## 10. Dependencies & assumptions
- bullet list
```

## Hard limits

- ≤ 2000 words (counted; verify stage will enforce with `wc -w`)
- Bullet > paragraph
- No filler, no "as an AI", no apology
- Every "Unknown" MUST be assigned a number (U1, U2, ...) for downstream reference
